Step 1: Substitute g(x) = 2x - 1 into f(x) = g(g(x)) - g(x) to get f(x) = g(2x - 1) - (2x - 1).
Step 2: Substitute g(x) = 2x - 1 into g(2x - 1) to get g(2x - 1) = 2(2x - 1) - 1.
Step 3: Simplify g(2x - 1) = 2(2x - 1) - 1 to get g(2x - 1) = 4x - 2 - 1 = 4x - 3.
Substitute g(2x - 1) = 4x - 3 into f(x) = g(2x - 1) - (2x - 1) to get f(x) = 4x - 3 - (2x - 1).
Simplify f(x) = 4x - 3 - (2x - 1) to get f(x) = 4x - 3 - 2x + 1 = 2x - 2.
Substitute x = 3 into f(x) = 2x - 2 to get f(3) = 2(3) - 2.
Simplify f(3) = 2(3) - 2 to get f(3) = 6 - 2 = 4. Final Answer
